#Intro to version control 

## Why version control systems?
-Efficient way of keeping tack of changes in a document
-keep track of changes in any type of document: txt, table, images

## Conflicts in version control
- Conflicts happens when someone changes the same part of a document at the same time 

##What is a commit
- save the changes made to files in a repository
- it does not have to be all files at a time 

## What is a repository?
- it is the whole of files and file versions, along with the history of changes made (commits)

## Difference between old and modern control systems 
- centralization vs distribution

